# Belt-and-suspenders against the merge-conflict pathology that the
# changelog fragments setup (`towncrier`, `changelog.d/`) is the real fix
# for: even with fragments in place, the periodic release-collation
# commit and any straggler hand-edits still touch CHANGELOG.md, and the
# `union` driver concatenates both sides of any append-only conflict
# instead of producing markers (you'll still want to eyeball the version
# numbers/ordering, but the rebase no longer stops). See
# `changelog.d/README.md`.
CHANGELOG.md merge=union
